Bill:
I find POST is very handy in cases like this when, in addition to handling
the request for work, I also want an audit log of the request along with the
final result of the request. In those cases, I define a representation that
contains the details of the state request that the client can send to the
server. When the work is done, the results are stored as a unique resource
in an archive that can be used for searching, reporting, etc.

